[[File:Paraglider.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A paraglider in the high atmosphere.]]
A '''para-wing glider''' or '''paraglider''' was a very light, single person, winged vehicle. It consisted of little more than a pair of wings and a [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] engine, which could be attached to a pilot's back. 

These gliders were used by tourists on [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]]. They were modified with a [[radar beacon]], [[Computer/Legends|comp]]-controlled navigational equipment and emergency [[Engine/Legends|thrusters]], making the gliders slower and less maneuverable than their unmodified counterpart but safer for tourists to use.<ref name="Galaxy Guide">[[Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin'', Second Edition]]</ref>

The downtrodden of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant's]] lower regions arranged para-wing races that utilized the tractor fields of the [[City/Legends|city's]] garbage pits.

The [[R-444 Imperial Sky Swooper]] used by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] was one well-known model of para-wing glider, alongside the [[ShadoWing-4]] and [[ShadoWing-6]] para-wing gliders most commonly used by civilian and by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]].

